This topic explains how to install <%= vars.product_name %> on AWS using Terraform. 

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

You can install <%= vars.product_name %> on AWS with either the Pivotal Application Service (PAS) or Pivotal Container Service (PKS) runtime.

To install <%= vars.product_name %> on AWS using Terraform, do one of the following:

* Install with PAS. See [Install with PAS Using Terraform](#terraform-pas).
* Install with PKS. See [Install with PKS Using Terraform](#terraform-pks).

## <a id="terraform-pas"></a> Install with PAS Using Terraform

To install with PAS using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Pivotal Operations Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/config-terraform.html).

1. Configure PAS. See [Configuring PAS](./configure-pas.html).

## <a id="terraform-pks"></a> Install with PKS Using Terraform

To install with PKS using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/config-terraform.html).

1. Configure PKS. See [Installing PKS on AWS](https://docs.pivotal.io/pks/installing-pks-aws.html).
